{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1389","heading":"Prohibition on attacks on United States servicemen on account of service","label":"1389 Prohibition on attacks on United States servicemen on account of service","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptI/ch67","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Uniform Code of Military Justice, referred to in subsec. (b), is classified generally to chapter 47 (§ 801 et seq.) of Title 10, Armed Forces."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of a simple assault, or destruction or injury to property in which the damage or attempted damage to such property is not more than $500, be fined under this title in an amount not less than $500 nor more than $10,000 and imprisoned not more than 2 years;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of destruction or injury to property in which the damage or attempted damage to such property is more than $500, be fined under this title in an amount not less than $1000 nor more than $100,000 and imprisoned not more than 5 years; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of a battery, or an assault resulting in bodily injury, be fined under this title in an amount not less than $2500 and imprisoned not less than 6 months nor more than 10 years.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Exception","label":"b .—Exception","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"This section shall not apply to conduct by a person who is subject to the Uniform Code of Military Justice.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Definitions","label":"c .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the term “Armed Forces” has the meaning given that term in section 1388;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the term “immediate family member” has the meaning given that term in section 115; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"means a member of the Armed Forces; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s1389/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs1389%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"includes a former member of the Armed Forces during the 5-year period beginning on the date of the discharge from the Armed Forces of that member of the Armed Forces.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
